{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-jsx","path":"/ar-AE/blog/akhbar/lifting-state-up","result":{"data":{"datoCmsMiscTextString":{"locale":"ar-AE","updatedAtText":"محدث","nextReadText":"اقرأ أيضا"},"datoCmsBlogPost":{"id":"106583930","locale":"ar-AE","originalId":"106583930","title":"Lifting State Up","seo":{"seoTitle":"Lifting State Up","seoDescription":"Every update goes through the same steps so the inputs stay in sync.","seoImage":{"seoImageUrl":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1627845998-article-9-cover-img.jpg?auto=format"}},"subtitle":"Every update goes through the same steps so the inputs stay in sync.","coverImage":{"coverImageData":{"images":{"sources":[],"fallback":{"src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1627845998-article-9-cover-img.jpg?auto=format&w=860","srcSet":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1627845998-article-9-cover-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.25&w=860 215w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1627845998-article-9-cover-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.5&w=860 430w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1627845998-article-9-cover-img.jpg?auto=format&w=860 860w","sizes":"(min-width: 860px) 860px, 100vw"}},"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpg;base64,"},"width":860,"height":430}},"meta":{"updatedAt":"2022-12-27T12:08:05.112+01:00","firstPublishedAt":"2021-08-01T21:29:50.056+02:00"},"categoryLink":{"title":"أخبار","id":"106584133"},"author":{"authorName":"Madeleine Moser","picture":{"authorPictureData":{"images":{"sources":[],"fallback":{"src":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1626962306-author-5-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.6&w=100","srcSet":"https://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1626962306-author-5-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.15&w=100 15w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1626962306-author-5-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.3&w=100 30w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/91338/1626962306-author-5-img.jpg?auto=format&dpr=0.6&w=100 60w","sizes":"(min-width: 60px) 60px, 100vw"}},"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpg;base64,"},"width":60,"height":60}}},"relatedPosts":[],"structuredBody":{"blocks":[],"links":[],"value":{"schema":"dast","document":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"Lessons Learned"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"There should be a single “source of truth” for any data that changes in a React application. Usually, the state is first added to the component that needs it for rendering. Then, if other components also need it, you can lift it up to their closest common ancestor. Instead of trying to sync the state between different components, you should rely on the "},{"url":"https://reactjs.org/docs/state-and-lifecycle.html#the-data-flows-down","type":"link","children":[{"type":"span","value":"top-down data flow"}]},{"type":"span","value":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Lifting state involves writing more “boilerplate” code than two-way binding approaches, but as a benefit, it takes less work to find and isolate bugs. Since any state “lives” in some component and that component alone can change it, the surface area for bugs is greatly reduced. Additionally, you can implement any custom logic to reject or transform user input."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"If something can be derived from either props or state, it probably shouldn’t be in the state. For example, instead of storing both "},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"celsiusValue"},{"type":"span","value":" and "},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"fahrenheitValue"},{"type":"span","value":", we store just the last edited "},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"temperature"},{"type":"span","value":" and its "},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"scale"},{"type":"span","value":". The value of the other input can always be calculated from them in the "},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"render()"},{"type":"span","value":" method. This lets us clear or apply rounding to the other field without losing any precision in the user input."}]}]}}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"106583930","locale":"ar-AE"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1034768456","1118752904","1936712626","2757196681","2850601048","3415878905","3879866231","4122876240"]}